A tragic shooting at an Omaha mall by 19-year-old Robert A. Hawkins resulted in the deaths of eight people before he turned the gun on himself.
Hawkins had a troubled past, including a recent breakup and job loss.
The community is devastated, with victims identified and survivors recounting harrowing experiences.
The shooter's actions were seemingly random, leaving behind a note expressing remorse.
Authorities are investigating how Hawkins obtained the assault rifle used in the attack.
The incident has sparked discussions on gun control and mental health awareness.
Grief counseling is being offered to those affected by this senseless tragedy.
